00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:46.990
So I wanted to walk you guys
through some of our really

00:10:46.990 --> 00:10:49.550
neat Localization support.

00:10:49.550 --> 00:10:53.100
To localize your game's
integration is pretty simple.

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:55.640
You add languages in the
console, provide translations.

00:10:55.640 --> 00:10:57.540
And we do all the hard
work for you.

00:10:57.540 --> 00:10:59.450
We pipe it all through to all
of the relevant places.

00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:02.375
If you go to the root of your
game configuration and hit Add

00:11:02.375 --> 00:11:04.290
Translations, you can select
your languages.

00:11:04.290 --> 00:11:05.710
And off you go.

00:11:05.710 --> 00:11:08.120
Now remember, once you've added
a language here, you're

00:11:08.120 --> 00:11:10.140
committing to providing
translations for all the

00:11:10.140 --> 00:11:12.130
strings that you send
us, all the

00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:13.680
achievement names, et cetera.

00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:16.500
And we don't want you to tick
all the boxes, so that it

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:18.460
looks like you're really
Localized, but

00:11:18.460 --> 00:11:20.000
not actually do it.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:21.240
You can also change the
default locale here.

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.760
So if you don't want
English to be the

00:11:22.760 --> 00:11:24.711
default, you can do that.

00:11:24.711 --> 00:11:27.590
For leaderboards and
achievements, translation are

00:11:27.590 --> 00:11:30.550
super, super simple.

00:11:30.550 --> 00:11:32.350
When your game is in Draft Mode,
you just type in the new

00:11:32.350 --> 00:11:34.010
title and go.

00:11:34.010 --> 00:11:36.150
If you don't do it, you can
get a nice, big error.

00:11:36.150 --> 00:11:38.640
It's says pretty clear what's
going on there.

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.100
I also want to talk about
leaderboard formatting.

00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:42.890
We have this really nifty stuff
here that's really nice

00:11:42.890 --> 00:11:44.160
for localization.

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:46.220
And it has other applications
too.

00:11:46.220 --> 00:11:48.280
First of all, you can have
currency leaderboards.

00:11:48.280 --> 00:11:50.020
And you can set that to a
number of international

00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:51.350
currencies.

00:11:51.350 --> 00:11:52.860
So we use the symbol for
that currency when

00:11:52.860 --> 00:11:55.080
we display the score.

00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:58.450
You might think though, that for
international currencies,

00:11:58.450 --> 00:12:01.970
you can just put the local
currency in for each locale,

00:12:01.970 --> 00:12:04.510
and it will format the
score locally.

00:12:04.510 --> 00:12:07.290
However, that is not the case.

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:11.240
So if you set your score to Yen
here, if I go back to US

00:12:11.240 --> 00:12:13.200
English, it will be Yen.

00:12:13.200 --> 00:12:14.670
And you might not want that.

00:12:14.670 --> 00:12:17.250
So this is a really good use
case for our custom score

00:12:17.250 --> 00:12:19.480
formatting, not the only
one, by a long way.

00:12:19.480 --> 00:12:22.400
But it's one I wanted
to highlight here.

00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:25.570
If I wanted to use dollars in
America and Yen in Japan, I

00:12:25.570 --> 00:12:28.135
configure an integer and
add a custom unit.

00:12:28.135 --> 00:12:30.650
Once I've done that, I've
committed to translating the

00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:33.300
plurals for that language,
for that unit.

00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:35.430
American English, it's easy.

00:12:35.430 --> 00:12:39.170
Japanese, I've decided just to
use the symbol, because I want

00:12:39.170 --> 00:12:41.550
to make sure I get it right.

00:12:41.550 --> 00:12:43.350
So I'm just going to do that.

00:12:43.350 --> 00:12:45.960
And as you'll notice,
the plural options

00:12:45.960 --> 00:12:47.230
are different there.

00:12:47.230 --> 00:12:48.580
We're pretty comprehensive
about that.

00:12:48.580 --> 00:12:51.560
So if you go to a language such
as Polish, you'll see we

00:12:51.560 --> 00:12:53.420
ask you to pluralize all
the different plural

00:12:53.420 --> 00:12:54.700
cases in that language.

00:12:54.700 --> 00:12:56.310
So if you're putting in
translation requests to

00:12:56.310 --> 00:12:59.270
external team, you might want
to bear that in mind.

00:12:59.270 --> 00:13:00.970
You can also use this as
a guideline when you're

00:13:00.970 --> 00:13:02.480
designing your leaderboards
in the first place.

00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:04.930
It might spark off
a few ideas.

00:13:04.930 --> 00:13:06.480
You can be pretty creative
as well.

00:13:06.480 --> 00:13:08.180
But there's a couple
of constraints.

00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:09.670
It's always a suffix.

00:13:09.670 --> 00:13:10.870
And in right to left languages,

00:13:10.870 --> 00:13:12.730
it would be a prefix.

00:13:12.730 --> 00:13:14.690
So what do you need?

00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:16.070
When you've added a language,
you're saying, I'm going to

00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:17.510
translate all this stuff.

00:13:17.510 --> 00:13:19.850
We make it pretty easy in that,
if you're testing, the

00:13:19.850 --> 00:13:21.570
descriptions can be optional.

00:13:21.570 --> 00:13:23.850
And the leaderboard units, as
you saw, you can change it

00:13:23.850 --> 00:13:25.230
around between different
languages.

00:13:25.230 --> 00:13:27.880
So you can have a custom one, in
English, and just plain old

00:13:27.880 --> 00:13:29.540
integer for the rest of them.

00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:33.374
If we don't have the unit, then
we'll just leave it off.

00:13:33.374 --> 00:13:35.920
A couple of nuances as well--

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:37.820
so you know, in the Play Store,
they have Localized

00:13:37.820 --> 00:13:38.520
Image Assets.

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:40.250
We do not have that yet.

00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:43.130
So make sure that your images
that you use for Achievement

00:13:43.130 --> 00:13:45.580
icons, leaderboard icons,
and so on are language

00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:46.300
independent.

00:13:46.300 --> 00:13:47.866
Otherwise, it looks
kind of weird.

00:13:47.866 --> 00:13:51.870
You also want to make sure
that, although you have a

00:13:51.870 --> 00:13:54.060
store entry and you have
configured translations for

00:13:54.060 --> 00:13:58.650
what appears in the Play Store
app, on other countries.

00:13:58.650 --> 00:14:00.530
This is unrelated to
what appears in the

00:14:00.530 --> 00:14:02.630
Game Services in Game.

00:14:02.630 --> 00:14:04.600
So if you've set all those
translations, you may have to

00:14:04.600 --> 00:14:06.380
just click them across.

00:14:06.380 --> 00:14:08.990
And also, if you're end game
locales are from the ones you

00:14:08.990 --> 00:14:11.890
have configured, there will be
a slight mismatch there.

00:14:11.890 --> 00:14:14.210
So there could be cases where
your game supports different

00:14:14.210 --> 00:14:16.770
languages to the ones you've put
in the Play Store config.

00:14:16.770 --> 00:14:17.955
Some people do that.

00:14:17.955 --> 00:14:19.930
We also do some pretty
cool fall-backs.

00:14:19.930 --> 00:14:22.443
So if you have a Canadian-French
player, but

00:14:22.443 --> 00:14:25.160
you've only got French-French
translations, we'll do that.

00:14:25.160 --> 00:14:29.280
We won't make them go English,
which is really nice.

00:14:29.280 --> 00:14:29.890
All right.

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:32.100
So I think we're
ready to test.

00:14:32.100 --> 00:14:32.495
We're good.

00:14:32.495 --> 00:14:34.916
How do we get some
beta testers?

00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:35.810
DANIEL GALPIN: All right.

00:14:35.810 --> 00:14:40.150
So again, to make things clear,
Game Services in the

00:14:40.150 --> 00:14:42.890
console are actually separate
from the regular Google Play

00:14:42.890 --> 00:14:43.760
Developer console.

00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:46.060
And part of the reason why is,
obviously, Game Services

00:14:46.060 --> 00:14:47.840
covers multiple platforms.

00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:50.310
And so when you're actually
talking about beta testers,

00:14:50.310 --> 00:14:52.540
you're actually talking about
beta testers that could be for

00:14:52.540 --> 00:14:53.190
any of these platforms.

00:14:53.190 --> 00:14:56.580
We have a separate place
in the services to

00:14:56.580 --> 00:14:58.600
actually set that up.

00:14:58.600 --> 00:14:59.640
And it's very simple.

00:14:59.640 --> 00:15:01.750
You just literally go
to Play Services.

00:15:01.750 --> 00:15:03.020
And you click Add Testers.

00:15:03.020 --> 00:15:04.090
And this is important.

00:15:04.090 --> 00:15:06.130
Because of course,
only testers can

00:15:06.130 --> 00:15:06.980
test unpublished games.

00:15:06.980 --> 00:15:08.910
And you kind of knew that one.

00:15:08.910 --> 00:15:10.150
We're kind of smart for you.

00:15:10.150 --> 00:15:13.680
We also make sure that only
testers can receive

00:15:13.680 --> 00:15:15.310
multiplayer invites.

00:15:15.310 --> 00:15:18.040
And so you won't accidentally
leak a really cool multiplayer

00:15:18.040 --> 00:15:20.090
game that you're working
on, just because

00:15:20.090 --> 00:15:22.830
you are testing it.

00:15:22.830 --> 00:15:25.160
Another thing, of course,
that's really useful for

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:28.300
developers and was asked very
early on is, please give me

00:15:28.300 --> 00:15:29.840
the ability to retest
Achievements.

00:15:29.840 --> 00:15:32.170
So at you can retest them
over and over again.

00:15:32.170 --> 00:15:36.230
And finally, you might want to
reset scores on leaderboards.

00:15:36.230 --> 00:15:37.590
And if you're doing multiplayer,
you might

00:15:37.590 --> 00:15:38.940
actually want to eliminate
all your

00:15:38.940 --> 00:15:41.340
multiplayer invites or rooms.

00:15:41.340 --> 00:15:44.770
So how do your testers
do this?

00:15:44.770 --> 00:15:47.360
Do you need to give each one of
your testers access to the

00:15:47.360 --> 00:15:50.570
Google Developer console?

00:15:50.570 --> 00:15:51.020
No.

00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:53.280
Actually, the good news is that,
you can build a website.

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:54.880
So your testers can reset
their own achievements,

00:15:54.880 --> 00:15:56.220
leaderboards, and multiplayer
rooms.

00:15:56.220 --> 00:15:58.450
And Jaewoong will show
us how to do it.

00:15:58.450 --> 00:15:59.000
JAEWOONG JUNG: Wow.

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:02.290
It's finally my turn.

00:16:02.290 --> 00:16:06.120
OK., how do you build a website
like this, where

00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:09.440
testers can reset
their game data?

00:16:09.440 --> 00:16:11.450
We must start with
registering our

00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:13.510
website on the Play console.

00:16:13.510 --> 00:16:16.880
Go to the Linked Apps tab,
click on that button, and

00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:23.120
choose Web, and enter basic
information, like the Launch

00:16:23.120 --> 00:16:26.780
URL, Save, and Continue.

00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:29.220
And click Authorize Your
App Now button.

00:16:29.220 --> 00:16:31.440
Otherwise, Google cannot
verify API

00:16:31.440 --> 00:16:33.710
calls from your site.

00:16:33.710 --> 00:16:35.740
Enter basic branding
information.

00:16:35.740 --> 00:16:38.900
This is only required
once for a project.

00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:40.780
And enter the Host Name.

00:16:40.780 --> 00:16:45.120
Only API calls from this host
will be authorized.

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:48.770
And finally, you're
given a Client ID.

00:16:48.770 --> 00:16:52.710
But unlike Android Apps, you
need the whole Client ID

00:16:52.710 --> 00:16:56.840
string to get all the tokens
from your website.

00:16:56.840 --> 00:17:00.350
So it's time to see how you
actually build your test

00:17:00.350 --> 00:17:02.960
website with the Client ID.

00:17:02.960 --> 00:17:05.560
Users must be signed into
Google to use the Games

00:17:05.560 --> 00:17:06.780
Services API.

00:17:06.780 --> 00:17:09.920
So let's add our Google+
Sign-In button

00:17:09.920 --> 00:17:11.940
to our website first.

00:17:11.940 --> 00:17:15.700
This is the standard Google+
Sign-In code, with a modified

00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:17.700
scope for the Games Services.

00:17:17.700 --> 00:17:23.800
And you want to specify the
Client ID here, like this.

00:17:23.800 --> 00:17:26.670
Also, handle the Sign-In
result with a callback

00:17:26.670 --> 00:17:27.659
function like this.

00:17:27.659 --> 00:17:29.420
And this is a very
simple version.

00:17:29.420 --> 00:17:32.660
It hides the Sign-In button
when it is successful.

00:17:32.660 --> 00:17:36.730
And it loads the error when
there are some problems.

00:17:36.730 --> 00:17:40.170
Now, the user is authorized
then, ready to call Games

00:17:40.170 --> 00:17:41.800
Services APIs.

00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:44.460
As an example, I'm going to
show you how to reset an

00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:47.130
achievement, while other restart
methods [INAUDIBLE]

00:17:47.130 --> 00:17:48.970
the same.

00:17:48.970 --> 00:17:51.960
Once the Sign-In is done, you're
given this special

00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:56.670
object called G-A-P-I, or gapi,
which is provided by

00:17:56.670 --> 00:18:00.230
Google API JavaScript Library.

00:18:00.230 --> 00:18:01.560
I remembered it.

00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:03.510
It provides many functions.

00:18:03.510 --> 00:18:06.680
But especially, this
client.request function is

00:18:06.680 --> 00:18:10.330
very handy, when you make
general API calls.

00:18:10.330 --> 00:18:13.470
You specify an API path.

00:18:13.470 --> 00:18:16.230
In this case, we're specifying
a path to set an achievement

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:18.290
with an Achievement ID.

00:18:18.290 --> 00:18:22.140
And specify a Calling Method,
like Post, Put, Get, or

00:18:22.140 --> 00:18:25.110
Delete, and a callback
function.

00:18:25.110 --> 00:18:26.070
And it's done.

00:18:26.070 --> 00:18:27.850
How simple is that?

00:18:27.850 --> 00:18:31.900
So now the Achievement will be
reset on the tester's device.

00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:33.235
Dan, is that right?

00:18:33.235 --> 00:18:35.600
DANIEL GALPIN: Not exactly.

00:18:35.600 --> 00:18:38.640
So right now, we've told the
server, great reset the

00:18:38.640 --> 00:18:39.130
Achievement.

00:18:39.130 --> 00:18:41.680
So the Achievement has now
been reset on the server.

00:18:41.680 --> 00:18:43.380
But it actually hasn't synced
to the device yet.

00:18:43.380 --> 00:18:46.420
And it doesn't sync immediately
there, unless you

00:18:46.420 --> 00:18:48.810
go and display our UI.

00:18:48.810 --> 00:18:50.980
So if you're not displaying our
UI, you're going to want

00:18:50.980 --> 00:18:53.450
to have the ability for your
testers to bring up the UI

00:18:53.450 --> 00:18:54.730
within your application.

00:18:54.730 --> 00:18:57.306
JENNIE LEES: What if I don't
want to build a website, Dan?

00:18:57.306 --> 00:18:58.530
DANIEL GALPIN: All
right, all right.

00:18:58.530 --> 00:18:59.740
That's a good point.

00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:01.940
So how many people here
don't want to build

00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:04.300
a website for this?

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:06.120
So the good news is that you can
actually reset them on the

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:07.640
device too.

00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:09.080
It's a little tricky, because
you actually have to go

00:19:09.080 --> 00:19:10.690
through the same flow.

00:19:10.690 --> 00:19:13.100
The good news is that we
actually offer you

00:19:13.100 --> 00:19:14.650
some APIs that help.

00:19:14.650 --> 00:19:17.030
First of all, you're going to
need up to two additional

00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:17.870
permissions.

00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:20.950
The great thing about using Play
Game Services is that you

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:23.400
don't actually need to have
internet permission or

00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:24.300
accounts permission.

00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.620
We handle all that in the
background for you.

00:19:26.620 --> 00:19:28.160
But if you're going
to want to reset

00:19:28.160 --> 00:19:31.520
Achievements for your testers.

00:19:31.520 --> 00:19:33.610
In a debug version of your
application, you're going to

00:19:33.610 --> 00:19:35.910
need these two additional
permissions, potentially.

00:19:35.910 --> 00:19:39.270
And after Sign-In is complete,
then you can get the current

00:19:39.270 --> 00:19:40.740
account name.

00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:44.680
Now, what's great about this,
is that you notice these two

00:19:44.680 --> 00:19:46.660
things in the bottom are
just very simple calls.

00:19:46.660 --> 00:19:48.970
And that's because they're
taking advantage of something

00:19:48.970 --> 00:19:51.830
called Base Game Activity, which
is a wrapper for our

00:19:51.830 --> 00:19:54.200
client library that handles a
lot of the boiler-plate code

00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:56.430
for handling errors
right for you.

00:19:56.430 --> 00:19:58.480
And it's part of Game Helper.

00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:00.820
And you can actually download
this off of

00:20:00.820 --> 00:20:01.540
the Developer site.

00:20:01.540 --> 00:20:03.770
And it gives you a lot of
insight into handling all of

00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:06.960
these cases in Google Play
Games Services--

00:20:06.960 --> 00:20:08.370
very, very cool.

00:20:08.370 --> 00:20:12.040
So then we just have to
get the Off Token.

00:20:12.040 --> 00:20:13.960
So now, the one thing that's
interesting about getting the

00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:16.670
Off Token is, we want to make
sure that the Scope that we're

00:20:16.670 --> 00:20:19.280
using, that we're trying to
fetch, matches the scope we're

00:20:19.280 --> 00:20:20.440
signing in with.

00:20:20.440 --> 00:20:23.930
So for example, if you wanted
to use both the Cloud Save

00:20:23.930 --> 00:20:28.970
APIs for App State and the Games
APIs, those are actually

00:20:28.970 --> 00:20:30.190
two separate Scopes.

00:20:30.190 --> 00:20:31.850
So you're going to want to
make sure they match.

00:20:31.850 --> 00:20:34.730
Otherwise, the system will go
and prompt you and say, you

00:20:34.730 --> 00:20:37.140
don't have a credential that
matches these Scopes.

00:20:37.140 --> 00:20:38.930
So we need to fetch that.

00:20:38.930 --> 00:20:40.340
So it's very, very
easy to do that.

00:20:40.340 --> 00:20:43.440
If you're using
BaseGameActivity/gamehelper,

00:20:43.440 --> 00:20:44.710
you can just call getScopes.

00:20:44.710 --> 00:20:46.130
And it'll nicely return
that for you.

00:20:46.130 --> 00:20:49.750
If you're not, that's how
you construct them.

00:20:49.750 --> 00:20:52.750
Then, we just fetch the token
from GoogleAuthUtil.

00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:55.620
Now, you note here, we're not
handling important exceptions

00:20:55.620 --> 00:20:57.970
like
UserRecoverableAuthException.

00:20:57.970 --> 00:20:59.495
After all, these are
just your testers.

00:20:59.495 --> 00:21:01.650
They'll see the log messages.

00:21:01.650 --> 00:21:03.200
Right?

00:21:03.200 --> 00:21:05.890
In all how seriousness, no,
there is a little bit more

00:21:05.890 --> 00:21:06.720
work to be done here.

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.450
And there are some things
that can go wrong.

00:21:08.450 --> 00:21:09.550
First of all, as I
said before, your

00:21:09.550 --> 00:21:11.430
Scope must match exactly.

00:21:11.430 --> 00:21:14.440
Otherwise, you'll get a
UserRecoverableAuthException.

00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:17.190
And of course, your token
may have expired.

00:21:17.190 --> 00:21:18.910
So there's nothing-- when you
actually call getToken,

00:21:18.910 --> 00:21:20.780
there's nothing that's part
of that call that goes and

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:22.240
automatically refreshes
the token.

00:21:22.240 --> 00:21:23.900
It's a pretty low-level API.

00:21:23.900 --> 00:21:26.730
But once you've done all this
work, you can pretty much do

00:21:26.730 --> 00:21:30.090
the exact same thing we
did on the server.

00:21:30.090 --> 00:21:34.860
Make a little HTTP client, call
that Rest API, and boom,

00:21:34.860 --> 00:21:36.090
we've now reset the
achievement.

00:21:36.090 --> 00:21:38.440
Now even though we've done
this on the device.

00:21:38.440 --> 00:21:43.430
We still have to go and call
the Games Services UI for

00:21:43.430 --> 00:21:45.820
displaying Achievements, in
order to force the client to

00:21:45.820 --> 00:21:47.970
pull those down.

00:21:47.970 --> 00:21:50.420
It's also just as easy to call
the Management API, if you

00:21:50.420 --> 00:21:51.860
want to reset the scores.

00:21:51.860 --> 00:21:52.980
As long as you have
that token, the

00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:55.690
world is your oyster.

00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:57.310
And again, you'll want to
invalidate the cache.

00:21:57.310 --> 00:21:59.990
You can also do it by calling
one of our APIs here and

00:21:59.990 --> 00:22:02.780
simply saying, forceReload
on all of these things--

00:22:02.780 --> 00:22:05.520
so very, very easy to make sure
that you continue to test

00:22:05.520 --> 00:22:09.730
leaderboards and Achievements,
again and again and again.

00:22:09.730 --> 00:22:11.850
So now, we're ready
to publish.

00:22:11.850 --> 00:22:15.606
It's time for the PM to
take all the credit.

00:22:15.606 --> 00:22:18.310
JENNIE LEES: This is
my favorite part,

00:22:18.310 --> 00:22:18.700
pushing stuff live--

