DANIEL GALPIN: Taking
the credit.

00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:21.610
JENNIE LEES: --breaking out of
there, fixing all the bugs,

00:22:21.610 --> 00:22:24.530
making people do it for me.

00:22:24.530 --> 00:22:27.460
So lets get our game
out there.

00:22:27.460 --> 00:22:30.720
But a few things just to bear
in mind, before you go live,

00:22:30.720 --> 00:22:33.470
before you hit the big
switch, so to speak.

00:22:33.470 --> 00:22:36.180
First of all, assets, we've
seen this in testing, that

00:22:36.180 --> 00:22:39.020
people forget to change their
placeholder assets.

00:22:39.020 --> 00:22:41.650
You need to make sure that you
have all the assets there and

00:22:41.650 --> 00:22:45.060
that you update them from
placeholders and don't just

00:22:45.060 --> 00:22:46.430
have 512 x 512.

00:22:46.430 --> 00:22:48.185
Insert Image Here going out
there in the world.

00:22:48.185 --> 00:22:49.300
That's not so good.

00:22:49.300 --> 00:22:52.100
Our console does give you a nice
little checklist, when

00:22:52.100 --> 00:22:54.690
you go to publish, saying, hey,
we're missing this stuff.

00:22:54.690 --> 00:22:56.150
So it's pretty simple
to make sure you've

00:22:56.150 --> 00:22:57.070
got that all right.

00:22:57.070 --> 00:22:59.110
And if you had descriptions
that were missing or

00:22:59.110 --> 00:23:01.360
placeholder translations,
like [INAUDIBLE]

00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:04.630
or something, you probably
want to change those too.

00:23:04.630 --> 00:23:08.360
So as Dan mentioned, we have
two different kinds of

00:23:08.360 --> 00:23:09.170
publishing.

00:23:09.170 --> 00:23:12.740
You can publish both to the
services and to Google Play.

00:23:12.740 --> 00:23:14.660
Now, in which order?

00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:16.270
Well, pretty simple, right,
you want to make sure the

00:23:16.270 --> 00:23:18.400
services work, before you
actually upload and APK that

00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:19.350
calls those APIs.

00:23:19.350 --> 00:23:22.550
If you do it the other way
around, things break.

00:23:22.550 --> 00:23:24.230
Breaking isn't good.

00:23:24.230 --> 00:23:28.790
The user experience is pretty
bad, if you put stuff out

00:23:28.790 --> 00:23:29.150
doesn't work.

00:23:29.150 --> 00:23:32.020
So we also want to make sure
that you publish it first, so

00:23:32.020 --> 00:23:33.650
you can go through the
validation checklist.

00:23:33.650 --> 00:23:35.600
Because there will be stuff that
goes wrong, and you want

00:23:35.600 --> 00:23:36.680
to make sure there's
no validation

00:23:36.680 --> 00:23:39.670
errors in that process.

00:23:39.670 --> 00:23:42.460
So once you are published, we
have a nice little treat in

00:23:42.460 --> 00:23:43.770
store for you .

00:23:43.770 --> 00:23:45.750
As you get more users,
you will get badges.

00:23:45.750 --> 00:23:46.880
We love badges.

00:23:46.880 --> 00:23:48.180
Badges are great.

00:23:48.180 --> 00:23:49.395
So you unlock some
Achievements of

00:23:49.395 --> 00:23:51.070
your very, very own.

00:23:51.070 --> 00:23:54.020
And you can get leaderboard
badge, and achievement badge,

00:23:54.020 --> 00:23:57.120
and a multiplayer badge, if you
use all three, in the Play

00:23:57.120 --> 00:23:58.290
Store, right there.

00:23:58.290 --> 00:23:59.380
And your apps will stand out.

00:23:59.380 --> 00:24:00.940
And people will know that you've
got these really cool

00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:02.800
services there.

00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:05.260
However, they're not just given
out because you had the

00:24:05.260 --> 00:24:06.590
leaderboards in the config.

00:24:06.590 --> 00:24:09.440
Or we don't snoop your APK and
check you're calling the APIs

00:24:09.440 --> 00:24:10.290
from there.

00:24:10.290 --> 00:24:12.830
We actually look at how much
your feature is being used.

00:24:12.830 --> 00:24:14.820
And when we reach a certain
threshold, we

00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:16.130
will give you a badge.

00:24:16.130 --> 00:24:17.980
So you have to actually
integrate it.

00:24:17.980 --> 00:24:20.840
It's not just a token thing that
you can do to get more

00:24:20.840 --> 00:24:22.090
eyeballs in the store.

00:24:26.282 --> 00:24:29.150
And so far, we've really just
been talking about the one

00:24:29.150 --> 00:24:32.640
app, "Angry Fruits," as we all
now in love and will dream

00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:34.980
about for days to come.

00:24:34.980 --> 00:24:40.320
But what if the smash hit "Angry
Fruit" is $0.99, and

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:42.873
it's just not really getting
that much traction?

00:24:42.873 --> 00:24:43.930
It's just not doing well.

00:24:43.930 --> 00:24:47.270
And we want to try and launch
maybe a free version.

00:24:47.270 --> 00:24:50.620
Well, the good news is, we
