your web management
app, that Jaewoong

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:06.980
showed you how to write.

00:25:06.980 --> 00:25:10.440
And once you've got it full
of apps, what's in common?

00:25:10.440 --> 00:25:11.390
We've got all these apps.

00:25:11.390 --> 00:25:13.440
But how do we know which
one's which and

00:25:13.440 --> 00:25:14.360
what's going on there?

00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:17.700
So achievements and leaderboards
within the same

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:20.820
game configuration are
global, so to speak.

00:25:20.820 --> 00:25:24.500
And we'll talk a little more
about that in a moment.

00:25:24.500 --> 00:25:27.410
There's also multiplayer,
because our system basically

00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:29.110
sees them all as one game.

00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:31.516
So they all play multiplayer
together.

00:25:31.516 --> 00:25:33.200
DANIEL GALPIN: That's
too much work.

00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:36.720
And besides, the free version
doesn't have the levels.

00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:38.810
So we have a way of
handling that.

00:25:38.810 --> 00:25:40.390
So first of all, you're going to
want to prevent people who

00:25:40.390 --> 00:25:42.030
