regardless of whether they

00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:55.940
actually have the game.

00:25:55.940 --> 00:25:58.440
Because it's one way of
directing people to the game.

00:25:58.440 --> 00:26:02.130
So what we suggest you do is
just handle this gracefully.

00:26:02.130 --> 00:26:04.330
Consider it an opportunity to
upsell someone to the premium

00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:06.440
version or to the new
version of the game.

00:26:06.440 --> 00:26:09.160
And we have a lot more
information about multiplayer

00:26:09.160 --> 00:26:12.720
coming on, in sessions that are
going to be in this room.

00:26:12.720 --> 00:26:14.130
So just stay tuned here.

00:26:14.130 --> 00:26:16.570
And you'll learn all sorts of
great stuff about how to

00:26:16.570 --> 00:26:17.500
implement multiplayer.

00:26:17.500 --> 00:26:20.590
And also, the Advance Game
Topics talk talks about more

00:26:20.590 --> 00:26:22.800
than just multiplayer, but has
a lot of really, really great

00:26:22.800 --> 00:26:26.180
info about how to
implement games.

00:26:26.180 --> 00:26:30.580
So there are a few cases where
you might want to prefer one

00:26:30.580 --> 00:26:32.770
version of your game over
others, however, when someone

00:26:32.770 --> 00:26:35.100
gets invited to it.

00:26:35.100 --> 00:26:36.640
Jaewoong, how do
we set that up?

