in the first place, as many as
you want, as long as you go

00:27:45.680 --> 00:27:47.810
under the limit that the
console gives you.

00:27:47.810 --> 00:27:50.270
And it's pretty much
exactly the same.

00:27:50.270 --> 00:27:53.300
And I'll just walk you through
how that works, when you've

00:27:53.300 --> 00:27:56.330
got a game that's live and a
game that's in development, at

00:27:56.330 --> 00:27:57.790
the same time.

00:27:57.790 --> 00:28:00.915
So your game out there, "Angry
Fruit" has three achievements.

00:28:00.915 --> 00:28:03.060
And your users are super,
super happy.

00:28:03.060 --> 00:28:04.010
And they want some more.

00:28:04.010 --> 00:28:06.340
So you add some more,
brilliant.

00:28:06.340 --> 00:28:09.560
And at the same time, you're
going to change the visuals on

00:28:09.560 --> 00:28:11.490
the existing achievements.

00:28:11.490 --> 00:28:13.990
Now, while your version is
out there and your new

00:28:13.990 --> 00:28:18.440
achievements are in draft mode,
