00:28:47.280 --> 00:28:48.660
The game doesn't
have the calls.

00:28:48.660 --> 00:28:51.180
Or the APK doesn't have the
code in there to do it.

00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:54.310
And in order to unlock it, they
need to get the new game.

00:28:54.310 --> 00:28:56.930
So that's a great opportunity
for an upsell.

00:28:56.930 --> 00:28:57.330
Don't you think?

00:28:57.330 --> 00:29:00.400
You've got this achievement
list and a description.

00:29:00.400 --> 00:29:02.630
Make the descriptions say, only
available in the brand

00:29:02.630 --> 00:29:06.410
new smash hit "Angry Fruit
Fall." Or you can upgrade the

00:29:06.410 --> 00:29:08.910
original APK and add in the
calls to unlock the new

00:29:08.910 --> 00:29:09.940
achievements in there.

00:29:09.940 --> 00:29:11.250
JAEWOONG JUNG: Well,
you know what?

00:29:11.250 --> 00:29:14.460
There is something they
cannot change.

00:29:14.460 --> 00:29:15.710
Let me show you.

00:29:18.360 --> 00:29:22.260
So before an achievement is
published, you can't really

00:29:22.260 --> 00:29:24.070
change its type.

00:29:24.070 --> 00:29:27.450
A [INAUDIBLE] achievement can
be changed to an incremental

00:29:27.450 --> 00:29:30.700
achievement or to a hidden
achievement.

00:29:30.700 --> 00:29:35.090
But once you make a choice and
publish it, the tie becomes

00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:41.390
permanent and cannot
be changed anymore.

00:29:41.390 --> 00:29:44.730
Leaderboards have something that
becomes permanent after

00:29:44.730 --> 00:29:46.270
publishing too.

00:29:46.270 --> 00:29:47.710
Let's look at this one.

00:29:47.710 --> 00:29:52.890
The top player, who remarkably
resembles me, is smiling,

00:29:52.890 --> 00:29:55.830
because he's leading on
a public leaderboard.

00:29:55.830 --> 00:29:58.590
He's the best to player in the
world, although there are only

00:29:58.590 --> 00:30:01.300
nine players at the moment.

00:30:01.300 --> 00:30:05.110
However, if the developer
changes the leaderboard

00:30:05.110 --> 00:30:09.370
ordering, the player will
suddenly find himself at the

00:30:09.370 --> 00:30:11.920
bottom of the leaderboard
and won't be

00:30:11.920 --> 00:30:14.460
able to smile anymore.

00:30:14.460 --> 00:30:17.470
Basically, we don't want to take
away something our user

00:30:17.470 --> 00:30:19.680
already earned.

00:30:19.680 --> 00:30:24.060
If a player, has earned rank, he
or she must be able to keep

00:30:24.060 --> 00:30:27.250
it until someone else beats
his or her score.

00:30:27.250 --> 00:30:30.700
In the same vein, you can't
re-publish the leaderboards or

00:30:30.700 --> 00:30:31.880
achievements.

00:30:31.880 --> 00:30:34.960
We'll apply the same thinking
when we introduce the new

00:30:34.960 --> 00:30:37.350
resource types in the future.

00:30:37.350 --> 00:30:44.250
DANIEL GALPIN: So looking at
that leaderboard, those two

00:30:44.250 --> 00:30:47.240
top scores look really
