Hiding a player is
really simple.

00:31:26.950 --> 00:31:29.940
This short JavaScript code,
using the gapi object is

00:31:29.940 --> 00:31:32.690
everything you need to write.

00:31:32.690 --> 00:31:36.110
The hide method is a plain
RESTful API, where hidden

00:31:36.110 --> 00:31:37.900
players are represented
as a [INAUDIBLE]

00:31:37.900 --> 00:31:39.850
resource in your game.

00:31:39.850 --> 00:31:43.290
So basically, you're
posting two new

00:31:43.290 --> 00:31:45.470
entries to the resource.

00:31:45.470 --> 00:31:49.360
And for that, you only need to
your own application ID, which

00:31:49.360 --> 00:31:52.850
you already know, and the player
ID you want a hide.

00:31:52.850 --> 00:31:55.060
Where do you get the player
IDs of the [INAUDIBLE]

00:31:55.060 --> 00:31:56.080
users?

00:31:56.080 --> 00:32:00.780
They are included in the
userboard score responses.

00:32:00.780 --> 00:32:06.280
After calling the hide method
with the two cheaters' IDs,

00:32:06.280 --> 00:32:07.030
they are hidden.

00:32:07.030 --> 00:32:09.660
And the leaderboard
is cleaned.

00:32:09.660 --> 00:32:13.030
JENNIE LEES: Wait, wait, wait,
you just hid my score.

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:14.290
But I'm not a cheater.

00:32:14.290 --> 00:32:19.780
I spent all night, like 24
hours, playing your game.

00:32:19.780 --> 00:32:20.773
Fix it.

00:32:20.773 --> 00:32:24.000
JAEWOONG JUNG: Oh, don't
worry, because

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:26.110
hiding is not banning.

00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:28.060
Hidden users can still
play the game.

00:32:28.060 --> 00:32:31.505
And their scores are still
recorded in the Google server.

00:32:31.505 --> 00:32:34.750
They just won't appear in
the game's leaderboards.

00:32:34.750 --> 00:32:36.750
Let me explain why
this matters,

00:32:36.750 --> 00:32:39.260
again with an example.

00:32:39.260 --> 00:32:41.070
It turns out Jennie
wasn't actually a

00:32:41.070 --> 00:32:42.320
cheater, as she said.

00:32:42.320 --> 00:32:44.330
And she just loves this
game so much.

00:32:44.330 --> 00:32:47.570
And she got disappointed because
you hid her scores.

00:32:47.570 --> 00:32:50.120
She made post something on
reddit, unless you do

00:32:50.120 --> 00:32:53.210
something to her.

00:32:53.210 --> 00:32:58.430
And this is why you need
the unhide player API.

00:32:58.430 --> 00:33:01.310
And you only need to call
this simple method

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:03.210
to revive her scores.

00:33:03.210 --> 00:33:07.120
Her scores will be restored,
normally, within a few hours.

00:33:07.120 --> 00:33:11.550
And as I explained earlier,
hidden player list is a list

00:33:11.550 --> 00:33:13.280
resource in your application.

00:33:13.280 --> 00:33:19.750
So what this call does is
essentially deleting a player

00:33:19.750 --> 00:33:22.510
from the list.

00:33:22.510 --> 00:33:24.100
But here's the problem.

00:33:24.100 --> 00:33:26.340
How do you know her player ID?

